race.comment: SUPER SOLAR (1) is a durable veteran who has been very consistent throughout his career and is at his best over a mile. He will be peaking third up, and he still has another win or 2 left in him. TRIPLE TIME (3) showed a good turn of foot when clearing his maiden status here in his penultimate start, and then tried to lead all the way at Moe last time out, fading late to end up in fifth. With a more patient ride this time, he can bounce straight back into the money. JOHNICH (7) built strongly to a well-deserved maiden win here 5 weeks ago, and has been back to the jumpouts since then. He has plenty of scope, so stick with him. NORWOODS (2) is a consistent gelding who is always worth including in all combinations.
